metadata.name: This Little Light of Mine
metadata.description: Below the rumble of the Manhattan Bridge lies a dark space where street vendors and loiterers escape the frantic energy of Chinatown. Amidst that darkness, small leaks of sunlight bring clarity to the graffiti and art that tell stories of the city while a certain New Yorker works to keep his sunkissed-space clean. Itâ€™s a unique scene, and one that will change constantly depending on the obscure angles of light, refreshed street art and movement of the city locals.
